title: BBC, PBS -  New York
description:
BBC, PBS -  New York

This nine-part 17,5 hour television event explores New York City's rich history as premier laboratory of modern life. A sweeping narrative covering nearly 400 years and 400 square miles. It reveals a complex and dynamic city that has played an unparalleled role in shaping the nation and the reflecting its ideals.

New York - 1 - Country And The City.avi
New York - 2 - Order And Disorder.avi
New York - 3 - Sunshine And Shadow.avi
New York - 4 - Power And The People.avi
New York - 5 - Cosmopolis.avi
New York - 6 - City Of Tomorrow.avi
New York - 7 - City And The World.avi
New York - 8 - Center Of The World.avi
New York - 9 - Extras Selected Interviews.avi

The first five episodes of New York were broadcast in November 1999; the sixth and seventh episodes in the fall of 2001; and the eighth and final episode in September 2003. Made by Ric Burns (Ken Burns brother).

Made by PBS 1999-2003, screened by PBS and BBC.
(http://www.pbs.org/wnet/newyork)
